  "texts": [
    "As such, the use of thiazine and methylene blue-based photosensitizers ensures low toxicity in water, which is a critical factor for sustainable and environmentally friendly wastewater treatment practices (Kenry and Liu, 2022; Thandu et al., 2015).",
    "They also offer the potential for combination therapies, allowing for synergistic approaches to enhance wastewater treatment effectiveness.",
    "This can involve coupling photodynamic processes with other treatment methods to address a broader range of contaminants.",
    "The unique method of action of thiazine photosensitizers makes them less prone to common chemotherapeutic resistance mechanisms (Kenry and Liu, 2022; Barakat et al., 2022; Thandu et al., 2015).",
    "This characteristic enhances their reliability and effectiveness in the treatment of wastewater."
  ],
